<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-12T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-12T05:00:00-05:00" n="993" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867.602 Ot 81/258: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-12T12:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">April 12,
                                        1923—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received April 12—11:09
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>104. French High Commissioner presented yesterday to Angora
                            representative formal note of protest against adoption of the Chester
                            project by Assembly. Am following situation closely and will telegraph
                            details later.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>